By Haruna Salami The National Assembly resumed on Tuesday after 3 weeks break for Sallah, but quickly adjourned plenary over the loss of a member of the House Representatives, Hon Jude Ise-Idehen. Hon. Ise-Idehen was representing Ikpoba-Okha/Egor Federal Constituency in the House of Representatives before his death was announced on July 1, 2022. At the Senate plenary on Tuesday, Deputy Senate President, Ovie Omo-Agege who presided led the members to observe one minuteâ€™s silence in honour of the diseased member and after which the Senate adjourned to next day, Wednesday July 20, 2022.